# Clarification-First Rule

- If requirements are ambiguous, stop and ask clarifying questions.
- Never assume architecture intent, naming, folder placement, or expected behavior.
- If multiple valid implementations exist, present options and ask for confirmation.
- Do not silently decide unresolved trade-offs.
- Clarification is mandatory before implementation when ambiguity exists.
- For every task, share a plan and clear doubts first, then wait for explicit user go-ahead before writing code.
